OL,3,CTeacher accused of murder denied he
OL,4,Cused baby as 'plaything' for 'own
OL,5,Camusement'
OL,7,FHe then accused the defendant of
OL,8,Fgiving a "wholly false account" about
OL,9,Ffinding him in the bath and fearing he
OL,10,Fhad drowned.
OL,12,FMr Wright said: "I am going to suggest
OL,13,Fthis is all rehearsed. It is all made
OL,14,Fup by you to conceal what you really
OL,15,Fdid."
OL,17,FVarley said: "That's incorrect."
OL,19,FThe prosecutor said: "You thought you
OL,20,Fwould be able to cover it up as a
OL,21,Fdrowning."
OL,26,@pD@JOUpD@_O]tD@QOUwD@EO]yD@NOUyD@`O]{D@
OL,26,AVOU}D@JO]
